          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Intrinsic value is the fair value of the share on the grant date minus the exercise price the employee will pay. If the share is valued at Rs 250 and the option is granted at an exercise price of Rs 100, the intrinsic value is Rs 150 per option. For 1,000 options that is Rs 1,50,000, charged to the profit and loss account across the vesting period."
          }
