        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the Black Scholes method for ESOP?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Black Scholes is an option pricing model that estimates fair value using the share price, exercise price, expected life, volatility, risk-free rate and dividend yield, so it captures time value that the intrinsic value method ignores. An option granted at the money has zero intrinsic value but positive Black Scholes value, which is why fair value almost always produces a larger ESOP charge."
          }
